02/11/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- At least three people were killed in an explosion at the Rafo Onesti oil refinery in northeastern Romania on Wednesday (November 1st). Authorities say the three workers were doing repairs at the refinery, which is undergoing a total overhaul, when the explosion took place. According to Bacau Prefect Gabriel Berca, a gas leak likely caused the blast. (Mediafax, Focus - 01/11/06) 
